        priority                  // LCP element — skip lazy-loading, emit <link rel="preload">
        quality={85}              // good visual fidelity; shaves ~15-20% off file size vs default 75→100
        sizes="100vw"             // always full-viewport-width, so the browser picks the right srcset entry
        className="object-cover object-center"
      />
    </div>
  );
}
```

**Why each prop matters:**

| Prop | Reason |
|---|---|
| `fill` | Parent is `position: relative` + fixed height, so `fill` is correct instead of hard-coding `width={2400} height={1200}` which would break responsive layout |
| `priority` | Hero is almost certainly the Largest Contentful Paint element; skipping lazy-load avoids a Core Web Vitals penalty |
| `quality={85}` | 1.2 MB PNG → Next.js converts to WebP/AVIF automatically; 85 is a good balance |
| `sizes="100vw"` | Tells the browser the image is always full-width so it downloads the smallest sufficient srcset variant |
| `alt` | Descriptive text satisfies the a11y requirement (accessibility audit rule) |

