### Why each decision was made

```
fill + sized parent div
  └─ avoids specifying pixel dimensions on the <Image> itself while still
     satisfying f008's "explicit width/height" spirit – the parent div's
     aspect-[2/1] class IS the explicit sizing contract.

     (Alternatively you could write width={2400} height={1200} and drop the
      wrapper div, but `fill` + a responsive container handles every viewport
      without a fixed pixel size in the markup.)

priority
  └─ Hero images are almost always the Largest Contentful Paint element.
     Without this, Next.js lazy-loads it and tanks your LCP score.

formats: ["image/avif", "image/webp"]  in next.config.js
  └─ The 1.2 MB PNG is never sent to the browser as-is.
     Next.js re-encodes on first request and caches the result.
     Typical outcome: 150–300 KB delivered vs 1.2 MB source.
     This is the primary f007 (bundle budget) protection for images.

quality={85}
  └─ Next.js default is 75; bumping to 85 for a hero gives noticeably
     better fidelity on a large canvas without a dramatic size penalty.
```

